                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 5.48,
                                "byte_start": 73961,
                                "byte_stop": 95904,
                                "text": "The second case I have to announce is McCarthy against Bronson."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 5.48,
                                "stop": 19.135,
                                "byte_start": 95904,
                                "byte_stop": 150552,
                                "text": "The petitioner in this case is a prisoner who brought suit against various state prison officials alleging that they violated his constitutional rights by using excessive force when transferring him from one cell to another."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 19.135,
                                "stop": 29.175,
                                "byte_start": 150552,
                                "byte_stop": 190676,
                                "text": "Over petitioner\u2019s objection, the case was referred to a magistrate to conduct an evidentiary hearing and prepare proposed findings effect and conclusions of law."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 29.175,
                                "stop": 39.398,
                                "byte_start": 190676,
                                "byte_stop": 231636,
                                "text": "A federal statute authorizes the nonconsensual referral to a magistrate of prisoner petitions challenging conditions of confinement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.398,
                                "stop": 53.933,
                                "byte_start": 231636,
                                "byte_stop": 289732,
                                "text": "Thus, the question is whether an allegation of a single episode of unconstitutional conduct by prison officials is covered by that language, or whether the language instead includes only challenges to ongoing prison conditions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 53.933,
                                "stop": 60.078,
                                "byte_start": 289732,
                                "byte_stop": 314288,
                                "text": "The District Court and the Court of Appeals both held that both types of cases may be referred to a magistrate."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 60.078,
                                "stop": 68.18,
                                "byte_start": 314288,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In a unanimous opinion filed with the Clerk today, we agree with that interpretation of the statute and thus, affirm the judgment of the Court of Appeals."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
